  Paul Newman plays the title role of the world-weary detective Lew Harper. Harper's personal life is a shambles, and his professional life isn't any better, and money making cases are rare. A job materializes via a lawyer friend. Harper finds a tie and one last clean shirt, and drives out of the city to a private estate of the very rich. And thus begins a bewildering tale of kidnapping, betrayal, murder, and complicated characters.
